  "prompt": "Does cctv works during power cut?",
  "response": "Whether CCTV works during a power cut depends on several factors:\n\n1. Battery Backup\n- Some CCTV systems have built-in battery backup\n- These can continue recording for a limited time during power outages\n- Duration depends on battery capacity (usually 1-8 hours)\n\n2. Power Source\n- Wired systems typically stop working without electricity\n- Wireless/battery-powered cameras can continue functioning\n- Solar-powered cameras might also work during power cuts\n\n3. Type of System\n- IP cameras with network video recorders (NVR)\n- Analog cameras with digital video recorders (DVR)\n- Different systems have different power requirements\n\n4. Additional Power Solutions\n- Uninterruptible Power Supply (UPS)\n- Backup generators\n- Solar power systems\n\n5. Recommended Setup\n- Install battery backup or UPS\n- Use cameras with independent power sources\n- Consider hybrid systems with multiple power options\n\nTo ensure continuous surveillance during power cuts, choose a system with reliable backup power and discuss specific requirements with a security professional.",
